ImageObject.type: An image of the item. This can be a URL

WinAction,WinAction,relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. In RDFa

error.description: For failed actions, more information on the cause of the failure.

Indicates a potential Action, which describes an idealized action in which 
WinAction,WinAction,this thing would play an 'object' role.

endTime.description:
The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. 
WinAction,WinAction,FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For 
WinAction,WinAction,actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. 
WinAction,WinAction,John wrote a book from January to *December*. Note that Event uses 
WinAction,WinAction,startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates 
WinAction,WinAction,with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

instrument.description: The object that helped the agent perform the action. e.g. John wrote a book

object.description:
The object upon the action is carried out, whose state is kept intact or 
WinAction,WinAction,changed. Also known as the semantic roles patient, affected or undergoer 
WinAction,WinAction,(which change their state) or theme (which doesn't). e.g. John read *a 
WinAction,WinAction,book*.

result.description: The result produced in the action. e.g. John wrote *a book*.

startTime.description:
The startTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. 
WinAction,WinAction,FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to start. For

URL of a reference Web page that unambiguously indicates the item's
